# Trivy CVE allow-list — audited exceptions only.
#
# Every line must include the CVE ID + a rationale. NEVER blanket-skip.
# When a patched upstream lands or we migrate the dependency, REMOVE the
# corresponding line.

# CVE-2024-23342  python-ecdsa < 0.19.x  Minerva timing side-channel on ECDSA
# operations.
#
# Audited not-applicable to TFactory:
#   - Pulled in transitively by python-jose[cryptography].
#   - Our JWT use sets JWT_ALGORITHM=HS256 (HMAC), never EC. See
#     apps/web-server/server/config.py:JWT_ALGORITHM default.
#   - Minerva attacks the EC signing path — irrelevant when we never
#     invoke EC.
#   - CVE upstream notes: "no known patched version exists" as of the
#     2024-01-23 publication. We are not the only project blocked here;
#     a migration to pyjwt (which depends on cryptography, not ecdsa)
#     is filed as follow-up.
CVE-2024-23342
